00:04:58.500 --> 00:05:01.380
So if we did our math right,
it shouldn't overflow.

00:05:01.380 --> 00:05:04.350
In the case that it does,
we have these tarps here

00:05:04.350 --> 00:05:05.730
to contain all of the foam

00:05:05.730 --> 00:05:07.320
from not going everywhere in the yard.

00:05:07.320 --> 00:05:09.120
We hope for the best,

00:05:09.120 --> 00:05:10.323
plan for the worst.

00:05:11.579 --> 00:05:14.246
(bright music)

00:05:15.540 --> 00:05:17.370
We built these three frames for the tarps

00:05:17.370 --> 00:05:19.590
that would contain the
catalyst yeast solution.

00:05:19.590 --> 00:05:20.850
So when it was time to fill the pool,

00:05:20.850 --> 00:05:23.130
we could just cut the tarps
and it would pour out.

00:05:23.130 --> 00:05:24.300
The same way we cut the tarp

00:05:24.300 --> 00:05:26.010
when we added the bigger Orbeez.

00:05:26.010 --> 00:05:27.000
- I'm alive!

00:05:27.000 --> 00:05:27.833
- And Kevin.

00:05:29.015 --> 00:05:30.150
(motor whirring)

00:05:30.150 --> 00:05:31.500
It's go time, baby.

00:05:31.500 --> 00:05:35.100
We're probably like seven minutes out.

00:05:35.100 --> 00:05:37.863
Got a bunch of kids inside
are just rearing to get out.

00:05:38.910 --> 00:05:40.859
The challenge here is this water's warm.

00:05:40.859 --> 00:05:44.060
We didn't build these
containers big enough,

00:05:44.060 --> 00:05:45.780
so this will start rising.

00:05:45.780 --> 00:05:47.580
So it's sort of a race against the clock

00:05:47.580 --> 00:05:49.170
before it starts overflowing.

00:05:49.170 --> 00:05:50.580
We still have to add the soap,

00:05:50.580 --> 00:05:52.643
and then we have to add the food coloring.

